[src:singular-value-decomposition-deep/low-rank-approximation] The alternating projections algorithm exploits the fact that the low rank approximation problem, parameterized in the image form, is bilinear in the variables P or L .
[src:singular-value-decomposition-deep/low-rank-approximation] The bilinear nature of the problem is effectively used in an alternative approach, called variable projections.
