[src:singular-value-decomposition-deep/moore-penrose-inverse] A computationally simple and accurate way to compute the pseudoinverse is by using the singular value decomposition.
[src:singular-value-decomposition-deep/moore-penrose-inverse] For a rectangular diagonal matrix such as ⁠ $\Sigma$ ⁠, we get the pseudoinverse by transposing and taking the reciprocal of each non-zero element on the diagonal, leaving the zeros in place.
